  "text": "Evaluation of the test-retest data collected from a separate group of participants indicated that, pre and post carotid measurements were significantly correlated (r = 0.98 to 1.00; p < .001), not significantly different (p > .05) and the coefficient of variation ranged from 0.20 to 2.26 %. Pre and post brachial measurements were significantly correlated (p < .001) not significantly different (p > .05) and the coefficient of variation ranged from 0.45 to 2.71 %. Pre and post popliteal measurements were significantly correlated (p < .001) not significantly different (p > .05) and the coefficient of variation ranged from 0.32 to1.89 %. Coefficients of variation are similar to those reported by Dinenno et al. [CITATION_1] .",
